<h1 class="page-header">Getting Started</h1>
<div class="doc">
  <%= image_tag 'Start_page.png', alt: '' %>
  <div class="goals">
    <h1>Goals</h1>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <div class="message">
          <p>Create Your New Application</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <div class="message">
        <p>Let's get started! By the end of this step, we'll have a brand-spankin'-new (empty) rails app.</p>
      </div>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="steps">
    <h1>Steps</h1>
    <div class="message tip vertical-centerer">
      <i class="fa fa-info-circle fa-3x"></i>
      <div class="vertically-centered">
        <p>If you have <em>any</em> problems, don't hesitate to let me know!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h1>Step 1</h1>
    <blockquote>
      <div class="console">
        <span>Type this in the terminal where you want to create your new rails application:</span><pre>rails new suggestotron -m https://gist.githubusercontent.com/mathieugagne/11214649/raw/c22dfbe6bc628fc9222a91ac1ca68180fb3f368e/suggestotron.rb</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="message">
        <p>'rails new' creates a new rails project with the name you give.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="message">
        <p>In this case we told it to create a new project called <code>suggestotron</code>. We'll go into detail on what it created shortly.</p>
      </div>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
  <a name="step6"></a>
  <div class="step">
    <h1>Step 2</h1>
    <blockquote>
      <div class="console">
        <span>Type this in the terminal:</span><pre>cd suggestotron</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="message">
        <p>'cd' stands for change directory.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="message">
        <p>'cd suggestotron' makes suggestotron our current directory.</p>
      </div>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
  <a name="step7"></a>
  <div class="step">
    <h1>Step 3</h1>
    <blockquote>
      <div class="console">
        <span>Type this in the terminal:</span><pre>ls</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="message">
        <p>'ls' stands for 'list (stuff)'.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="message">
        <p>It shows you the contents of the current folder.</p>
      </div>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
  <a name="step8"></a>
  <div class="step">
    <h1>Step 4</h1>
    <blockquote>
      <div class="message">
        <p>Open the suggestotron folder as a project in your text editor.</p>

        <p>In <strong>Sublime Text 2</strong>, you can use the <code>Project &gt; Add Folder to Project...</code> menu option:</p>

        <p><%= image_tag "sublime_add_folder_to_project.png", alt: '' %></p>

        <p>Select your <code>suggestotron</code> folder from the file picker that opens. If everything works out Sublime should look something like this:</p>

        <p><%= image_tag "sublime_project_as_folder.png", alt: '' %></p>
      </div>
    </blockquote>
    </div>
    <div class="message">
      <p>You can see that <code>rails new</code> created a lot directories and
        files. The ones we want to focus on today are:</p>
      </div>
      <table class='table'>
        <tbody><tr>
          <th>File/Folder</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>app/</td>
          <td>Contains the controllers, models, and views for your application.  You will do most of your work here.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>config/</td>
          <td>Configure your application's runtime rules, routes, database, and more.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>db/</td>
          <td>Shows your current database schema, as well as the database migrations.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>public/</td>
          <td>The only folder seen to the world as-is. If you put files in here, they will be served directly without any processing by Rails.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>app/assets/</td>
          <td>This is where your images, JavaScript, stylesheets (CSS), and other static files should go. Modern rails apps use something called the Assets Pipeline, which combines all the JavaScript and CSS files in this directory into a single file for speediness.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody></table>
      <div class="message">
        <p>There is a lot more that <code>rails new</code> created. Probably enough to fill a book, so we're going to ignore them for now.</p>
      </div>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
  <div class="step next_step">
    <h1><span class="prefix">Next Step:</span></h1>
    <p class="link">Go on to <a class="link" href="add_the_project_to_a_git_repo?back=getting_started%23step8">Add The Project To A Git Repo</a></p>
  </div>
</div>